 who created of her the cornerstone for both his metaphysical and aesthetic systems. This spiritual courtship of the Divine Sophia deeply patterned the literary works and interrelationships not only of such prominent symbolist writers as Aleksandr Blok and Andrej Belyj, but brought to light religious eccentrics like Anna Schmidt in a scandalous fashion. Sophia’s influence ranged far beyond the narrower confines of literature and eventually provoked one of the most fascinating debates within the modern émigré Russian Orthodox Church through the offices of Sergej Bulakov, an apparent student of Solovev’s Sophiology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoésie russexHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aPoésie russexHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aRussian poetryxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aRussian poetryxHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aRussian poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSymbolism in literature. 0aSymbolisme dans la littérature. 0aSymbolisme dans la littérature. 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aPoetry. 4aReligion. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Philosophers.2bisacsh  aRussian orthodoxy.  aRussian philosophy.  aRussian poetry.  aRussian theology.  aSophiology.  aphilosophy and religion.  apoetry and philosophy.  areligious eccentric.  aspiritual courtship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920859940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208599423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889208599/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  